description.generated:
At a T-junction intersection, a truck lost control and veered over the center island, resulting in a series of collisions. The rear of the truck struck a passenger vehicle that was stationary at the intersection, propelling it into another waiting passenger vehicle on the same approach. Subsequently, the out-of-control truck crashed head-on into a passenger vehicle that was making a left turn toward the truck's direction of travel. This collision forced the turning car backward into a bus that was executing a right turn at the intersection.

During this chaotic incident, a pedestrian was crossing the road at the junction where the truck originated. Fortunately, the pedestrian was unharmed and managed to avoid any accidents despite the unfolding chaos around them. The scenario paints a picture of multiple collisions initiated by the truck's loss of control, affecting several vehicles and highlighting the potential dangers at traffic intersections.

The primary objective of this verification plan is to ensure the safety and efficacy of the perception and planning systems of an automated vehicle (AV) when approaching a T-junction intersection under complex and dynamic conditions.
